Okay, so we are actually still very, very far from Ubud.

We arrived in the beautiful Mantra Resort just after dusk. The Mantra is a very family friendly complex with bargain rates at the moment because unless you were actually considering the fleshpots of Bali, I assure you, it’s the right place to stay. A burnished sunset was upon us, lending the pools, the gardens and the chalets warm, golden light.

We were treated by Mantra tools to a complimentary drinks before dinner. I had a gin, don’t judge. Leo had a beer, which was well deserved, but hey. I had my drink, my son had his beer, when this happens, mum’s usually pretty happy.

I was expecting a reasonable level of service, but this was so much better than I could have hoped for, considering Ma’atra is one of the biggest restaurant/club/live music venues on the island. The spoiled mummy finally got a reasonably spa treatment after a long time and she was pretty impressed. Who knew that all she had to do was barricade herself in a spa during a typhoon?
